1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:01,967
<i>When two people meet bad luck
when they're together,</i>

2
00:00:02,100 --> 00:00:03,067
<i> they are cursed.</i>

3
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:05,100
<i>If I were you,
I'd have that removed.</i>

4
00:00:05,233 --> 00:00:06,900
<i>I know a way
to get rid of it.</i>

5
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:08,200
<i>I know something
happened,</i>

6
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:10,100
<i>because the Luna I met
in Manila</i>

7
00:00:10,233 --> 00:00:12,433
<i>is different from the Luna
I'm with now on this island.</i>

8
00:00:12,567 --> 00:00:14,467
<i> People change, Gio.</i>

9
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,867
<i>Yes, but I know
there's a reason.</i>

10
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,267
And that's what I want to know.

11
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:20,000
<i>- Sandro Soliman?
- You know him?</i>

12
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:22,733
<i> Someone is looking for him.</i>

13
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:23,833
<i> Could it be his family?</i>

14
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:25,967
<i>Good morning, sir.
How can I help you?</i>

15
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:28,933
<i>I'd just like to ask
if I could post this.</i>

16
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:31,600
<i>Oh, sorry, sir, but the
bulletin board</i>

17
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:34,500
<i>is only for hotel
programs and activities.</i>

18
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:37,433
<i>Why were you staring at my
brother like that?</i>

19
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,200
Okay. How many fingers
am I holding up?

20
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:41,800
- [KIKO] Three.
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

21
00:00:41,933 --> 00:00:43,433
How about this?

22
00:00:43,567 --> 00:00:44,600
One.

23
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,700
And this?

24
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:50,500
- Four.
- Wrong!

25
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:54,367
Oh, no! I think the venom
got into your brain.

26
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,067
- That's not good.
- You didn't let me finish.

27
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:59,167
Four plus one is five,
so that's five.

28
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:02,200
[CHUCKLES] You guys are funny.

29
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:04,400
Stop it, okay?

30
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:08,167
You're making everyone here
think that we're silly.

31
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:11,733
Kiko, are you sure you're okay?

32
00:01:11,867 --> 00:01:13,167
Yes, I'm fine.

33
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:15,667
I already got
first aid treatment,

34
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:18,033
and we went to the clinic
before we went home.

35
00:01:18,167 --> 00:01:20,833
They said it wasn't
poisonous.

36
00:01:20,967 --> 00:01:24,200
- I'm telling you, it's--
- Sari.

37
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:27,767
Sir, I'm just concerned
about them.

38
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:30,700
I don't want them
to get bad luck.

39
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:34,867
Well, I think there's
no harm

40
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,000
if we'd follow what
our elders say.

41
00:01:38,133 --> 00:01:40,900
See? You've brainwashed
the people here.

42
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:43,100
Martin, it's okay.

43
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:45,433
I don't believe it either.

44
00:01:45,567 --> 00:01:46,633
But--

45
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:51,067
[SARI] Okay, okay.

46
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:53,067
I won't insist anymore.

47
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,533
I'll stop.

48
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,500
[MARTIN] Finally, you're here.

49
00:02:01,533 --> 00:02:04,500
Okay, I think they'll have
a family meeting.

50
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:06,867
So, girls, let's go?

51
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,200
Come on.

52
00:02:08,967 --> 00:02:11,300
Bye, bro.
You take care, okay?

53
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:17,333
Oh, here's your fan.

54
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:20,533
Thank you, I thought you were
going to take it.

55
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:22,167
Of course not.

56
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:24,333
But thank you.

57
00:02:24,467 --> 00:02:26,800
I slept well last night.

58
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:28,367
Don't mention it.

59
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:38,100
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:03:30,567 --> 00:03:32,233
- Thank you.
- Okay.

61
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,600
[LEON] Why are you back
just now?

62
00:03:38,867 --> 00:03:40,200
Where have you been?

63
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,967
Is Justin here already?

64
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,467
He arrived a few
minutes ago.

65
00:03:44,367 --> 00:03:46,167
Where have you been, Luna?

66
00:03:47,233 --> 00:03:50,433
I went somewhere
with Gio.

67
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:54,167
Gio? Where did he take you?

68
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:57,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:03:57,433 --> 00:03:58,967
- He asked me to go with him.
- Where?

70
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,367
Justin, enough with the
questions, okay? I'm tired.

71
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:04,900
I'm tired, too.
You're not the only one.

72
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:07,933
You two should get
some rest.

73
00:04:08,067 --> 00:04:09,733
Go home, okay?

74
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:15,200
No need. I'll stay here.

75
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:16,533
What are you going to do here?

76
00:04:16,667 --> 00:04:18,300
[JUSTIN SCOFFS, CLICKS TONGUE]

77
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:20,333
I don't get it.

78
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:22,233
You get upset when
I'm not here,

79
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:23,767
and when I'm here,
you ask many questions.

80
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,300
What do you really want?

81
00:04:25,433 --> 00:04:28,600
I'm just asking what you're
going to do here, Justin.

82
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:33,467
Nothing. I'll just hang out
here and look around.

83
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,267
I'll keep an eye
on things.

84
00:04:39,233 --> 00:04:40,567
Suit yourself.

85
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:43,833
Just remember, don't cause
any trouble, Justin.

86
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:46,233
I won't. I promise.

87
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:47,400
You better behave, Justin.

88
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:53,967
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

89
00:04:54,100 --> 00:05:00,933
[MUSIC BECOMES UNSETTLING]

90
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:06,667
I think even though we ended
up doing treasure hunting,

91
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,367
the team building
was still a success, right?

92
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,733
Yes, I think it went great.

93
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:14,700
Even though we were teamed
up with the Almazans,

94
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:17,467
we were able to play
without any problems.

95
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:19,767
You know, I guess
it's a step

96
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,833
for us to be reunited
with the Almazans.

97
00:05:22,967 --> 00:05:24,000
What do you think, Gio?

98
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:30,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,500
It's alright.

100
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:36,100
Whatever you decide to do
with the Almazans,

101
00:05:36,233 --> 00:05:37,500
I'll be on board.

102
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:40,367
Are you still going to leave?

103
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:43,400
For now, no.

104
00:05:44,067 --> 00:05:45,133
Really?

105
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:46,400
That's good.

106
00:05:46,533 --> 00:05:49,767
Did the team building
change your mind?

107
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,867
[LUNA]<i> I left everything
</i> that happened in the past.

108
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,500
<i> This is who I am now.</i>

109
00:05:58,333 --> 00:05:59,667
<i> This is the Luna I know.</i>

110
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:02,867
<i> If you can't accept it,</i>

111
00:06:03,867 --> 00:06:05,767
<i>there's nothing I can do
about it.</i>

112
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,367
<i> So enough.</i>

113
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,233
No.

114
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:22,400
Just think of it as my way
of making it up to you.

115
00:06:22,533 --> 00:06:23,967
That's why I'm still here.

116
00:06:35,133 --> 00:06:36,033
[DOOR SLAMS]

117
00:06:36,733 --> 00:06:37,567
[YELLS]

118
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:39,967
[SCREAMING]

119
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:42,900
[YELLS]

120
00:06:47,367 --> 00:06:49,833
[YELLING CONTINUES]

121
00:06:49,967 --> 00:06:51,133
[LAMP THUDS]

122
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:09,300
[PETER SINGING]
<i> Happy birthday to you...</i>

123
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:14,967
<i>- Happy birthday to you...
- [LUNA] Oh!</i>

124
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:17,967
- [LUNA CHUCKLING]
<i> - Happy birthday...</i>

125
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:20,967
<i> Happy birthday...</i>

126
00:07:21,867 --> 00:07:22,900
[LUNA GRUNTS]

127
00:07:23,033 --> 00:07:27,633
<i> Happy birthday to you</i>

128
00:07:27,767 --> 00:07:29,767
<i>- Make a wish.
- 'Kay.</i>

129
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,033
[BLOWS]

130
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:35,500
<i> Yay! Thank you, babe!</i>

131
00:07:35,633 --> 00:07:37,733
<i> Anything for you.</i>

132
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:40,000
<i> Something is missing.</i>

133
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,500
<i> Where's my gift?</i>

134
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:45,033
[CHUCKLING]

135
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:48,867
<i> I love my gift!</i>

136
00:07:49,467 --> 00:07:54,333
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

137
00:07:54,467 --> 00:07:55,767
[LUNA] Peter...

138
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:04,300
[WAVES LAPPING]

139
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,300
Hey!

140
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,633
You okay?

141
00:08:14,767 --> 00:08:19,633
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:21,067
Can I have this one?

143
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:22,533
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

144
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:24,500
What happened?

145
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:28,633
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

146
00:08:28,767 --> 00:08:29,867
Okay.

147
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,633
I'll leave you here for now.

148
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:36,067
If you don't want to talk,
I won't force you.

149
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,400
I already know.

150
00:08:37,533 --> 00:08:44,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,267
She was broken
when we met.

152
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:58,767
Huh?
[CHUCKLES]

153
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,733
Weren't you guys
too young to be broken?

154
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:07,133
No, Monette.

155
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,600
We were together
a few years ago.

156
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:12,767
Huh?

157
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:19,867
- [DEVICE CHIMES SOFTLY]
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

158
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,900
When she ran away,

159
00:09:25,067 --> 00:09:27,933
I found her in Manila,
and we stayed together there.

160
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,467
Were you guys a couple?

161
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,433
I don't know.

162
00:09:35,567 --> 00:09:37,200
How can you not know?

163
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:44,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:09:46,867 --> 00:09:48,433
I was there
when she needed me.

165
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:53,400
I was there when
she just wanted me around.

166
00:09:57,867 --> 00:10:00,000
Then suddenly,
she left me.

167
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:03,167
And now...

168
00:10:05,033 --> 00:10:06,500
she acts like I don't exist.

169
00:10:07,867 --> 00:10:09,300
Yikes...

170
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:12,833
That's called "ghosting".

171
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,800
I guess.

172
00:10:17,633 --> 00:10:19,200
[MONETTE SIGHS SOFTLY]

173
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:20,867
All I know is...

174
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:23,500
she treated me like trash.

175
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:29,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,867
Do you still love her?

177
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:37,300
[CLICKS TONGUE]
Looks like it.

178
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:38,433
You wouldn't be like this

179
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:41,700
if you didn't still
have feelings for her.

180
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:43,033
[BOTTLE CLINKS]

181
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:46,167
[MOUTH CLICKS, SIGHS SHARPLY]

182
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,467
If you still love her,

183
00:10:49,767 --> 00:10:52,667
find the answers
to all your questions.

184
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,067
Then fight for it.

185
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:57,333
As long as you can,
as long as you want to.

186
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:01,133
But if you can't anymore...

187
00:11:04,033 --> 00:11:05,667
don't hurt yourself trying.

188
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:12,567
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

189
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:18,133
Here's your drink, sir.

190
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,200
Thank you.

191
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,800
The staff here
is very attentive.

192
00:11:20,933 --> 00:11:22,233
[CHUCKLES]

193
00:11:22,367 --> 00:11:25,467
Thank you for
the compliment, sir.

194
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,567
But we need cash.
[CHUCKLES]

195
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:29,367
You guys are funny.

196
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,633
Thank you.

197
00:11:30,767 --> 00:11:33,133
Maybe your bosses
are kind too,

198
00:11:33,267 --> 00:11:35,033
that's why you treat
guests like this.

199
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:37,933
[RAPHIE] Oh, our bosses now
are different, sir.

200
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:41,300
They're kind too,
but Sir Michael..

201
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:44,533
He was different. Not a
single bad bone in his body.

202
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:48,133
Rest in peace, Sir Michael.

203
00:11:48,267 --> 00:11:50,767
Yeah, I heard you're
under new management...

204
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:53,133
since you just reopened.

205
00:11:53,267 --> 00:11:55,000
Why did you close before?

206
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:57,367
Well, first,
because of the pandemic.

207
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,967
You know,
the whole world shut down,

208
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:00,567
so we had to as well.

209
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,933
But we reopened, sir.

210
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:05,700
Except then,
there was a fire.

211
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:06,900
A fire?

212
00:12:07,033 --> 00:12:10,333
[RAPHIE] Mm. Yes, sir.
But not the whole hotel.

213
00:12:10,467 --> 00:12:14,600
We just had to close again
for renovations.

214
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:17,200
So it was renovated.

215
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:20,833
But there aren't any signs
of a fire here.

216
00:12:20,967 --> 00:12:22,833
Your contractor
must be good.

217
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:24,200
Who handled it?

218
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:26,100
Oh! I don't know
about that, sir.

219
00:12:26,233 --> 00:12:29,167
My former boss
handled all that.

220
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:30,967
Oh, okay.

221
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:35,233
Sir, do you need
anything else?

222
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:38,600
Uh, no. I'm good.

223
00:12:38,733 --> 00:12:41,367
Thank you... Raphie.

224
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,600
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

225
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:45,200
You're welcome, sir.

226
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:50,900
[CLEARS THROAT] Please sign the
acknowledgment receipt, sir.

227
00:12:51,067 --> 00:12:53,033
And maybe add
your social media?

228
00:12:53,167 --> 00:12:54,433
Just kidding!

229
00:12:54,567 --> 00:12:58,033
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

230
00:12:58,167 --> 00:12:59,600
Thank you, sir!

231
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,067
Take care. Enjoy!

232
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:05,800
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:07,433
<i> The hotel was renovated.</i>

234
00:13:10,567 --> 00:13:11,733
<i> Is this what Dad meant</i>

235
00:13:11,867 --> 00:13:14,567
<i>when he said he worked on
a project here in Isla Solara?</i>

236
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:18,300
<i> Right here at Hotel 88.</i>

237
00:13:18,433 --> 00:13:24,533
[UNEASY MUSIC SWELLS,
THEN FADES]

238
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:26,400
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

239
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:30,967
[BOTH CLEAR THROAT]

240
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,533
[EDWARD] Let's eat.

241
00:13:32,667 --> 00:13:33,633
Yes.

242
00:13:34,967 --> 00:13:36,233
[PHONE CHIMES]

243
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:38,833
"Hi Jade. Where are you?

244
00:13:38,967 --> 00:13:40,400
Are we still meeting
Sari's grandpa today?"

245
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,100
Jade.

246
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,367
Lunch.

247
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,567
One hour.

248
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:53,967
I don't think
responding to messages

249
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:56,033
won't take long.

250
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:58,300
It doesn't matter.

251
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:01,133
Come on, eat.

252
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,267
I made it so I'm sure...

253
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,100
You're not going to poison me?

254
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,567
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

255
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:20,600
It's delicious.

256
00:14:25,867 --> 00:14:27,200
[EDWARD] Try it.

257
00:14:31,433 --> 00:14:32,333
Well?

258
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:35,233
It's good.

259
00:14:37,267 --> 00:14:38,733
[BOTH CHUCKLES]

260
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:44,267
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:14:48,967 --> 00:14:50,367
- Hey, Sari!
- Yes, Sir Kiko?

262
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,867
[KIKO] Can you tell
your grandfather that--

263
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,300
Shh!

264
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:55,033
Shh! Wait.

265
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:57,167
Stay! Stay there, sir.

266
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,567
[PHONE BUZZES, BEEPS]

267
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,400
[KIKO] H-Hello?

268
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:09,000
Sir Kiko, let's communicate
this way.

269
00:15:09,133 --> 00:15:10,900
I don't want Sir Martin
to catch us

270
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:12,767
talking about your
and Miss Jade's curse.

271
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:14,433
He's just behind me.

272
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:19,167
Wait a second.
Did I give you my number?

273
00:15:19,967 --> 00:15:22,300
Sir,
you're Sir Martin's brother.

274
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:25,267
I need to know all of my
boss's emergency contacts.

275
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:27,500
You're really impressive.

276
00:15:27,633 --> 00:15:29,533
Of course, sir!

277
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:31,633
[KIKO] Wait. Hang on.

278
00:15:31,767 --> 00:15:33,900
I just wanted to ask you

279
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:36,000
to tell your grandpa

280
00:15:36,167 --> 00:15:37,567
that we can't meet him today.

281
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:40,400
Jade hasn't been
responding to my messages.

282
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:43,833
Oh, sir! You can't delay
a curse.

283
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:46,100
It might get worse!

284
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:47,500
What will get worse?

285
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:49,700
[SARI] Oh! The...

286
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:50,833
You know, the...

287
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:54,200
What will get worse?

288
00:15:55,067 --> 00:15:57,000
Uh, sir, the...

289
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,133
uh, my... my...

290
00:15:59,133 --> 00:16:02,100
my head, sir! My head hurts
so bad!

291
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,633
This needs to be cured
immediately, right?

292
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:07,667
Of course, we have to tend to it
right away!

293
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:11,233
[SARI] I told you!
This headache of mine

294
00:16:11,233 --> 00:16:13,267
should be cured, sir! [GROANS]

295
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:15,167
Alright, Gramps.
I'll message you

296
00:16:15,167 --> 00:16:17,567
on how to get
to your destination instead.

297
00:16:17,567 --> 00:16:19,633
Ouch, my head hurts, sir!

298
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,000
[INAUDIBLE]

299
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:24,367
- [SARI GROANS]
- Huh? I thought you left?

300
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:27,567
Uh, no, I-- I just took
this call first

301
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:30,533
but I'm heading out now
I think it's from a scammer.

302
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:32,467
- Alright then...
- See you, Martin.

303
00:16:32,467 --> 00:16:34,033
- Sari, let's go!
- Yeah?

304
00:16:34,033 --> 00:16:36,600
I'll have Monette
get you some medicine.

305
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:41,033
[CLEARS THROAT]

306
00:16:50,233 --> 00:16:53,167
[LAUGHS] Jade, you can
take your time, you know?

307
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:56,400
- We have an hour, right?
- [JADE LAUGHS]

308
00:16:56,400 --> 00:17:03,367
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

309
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:08,433
[CLEARS THROAT]

310
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:13,267
By the way, how is...
how is...

311
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:15,300
Kiko doing?

312
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:21,433
Didn't he get bitten
by a-- a snake?

313
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:23,033
- Was it a snake?
- [JADE CHUCKLES]

314
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:24,733
He's doing fine. [LAUGHS]

315
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:26,733
It's like nothing even happened.

316
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:33,733
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

317
00:17:35,133 --> 00:17:36,733
Hey, guys! I didn't know
you were here.

318
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:38,533
- Ah, Uncle, eat with us!
- Dad.

319
00:17:38,533 --> 00:17:40,600
Oh Jade, have a seat.
Enjoy your lunch.

320
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,333
[LAUGHS] Hey, did you cook?

321
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:47,733
You should come by
more often, please! [LAUGHS]

322
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:50,233
You know, I don't remember
the last time you cooked, bud.

323
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:53,633
Dad, I actually
saved some for you.

324
00:17:53,633 --> 00:17:55,100
- You can eat it later.
- [ANDY CHUCKLES]

325
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:56,367
Alright, alright.

326
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,100
Good to see you.

327
00:17:58,100 --> 00:17:59,667
I hope to see you around
all the time.

328
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:02,467
See? When he cooks for you
I end up eating some too.

329
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:03,367
- [JADE CHUCKLES]
- Dad.

330
00:18:03,367 --> 00:18:05,500
Okay, I get it.
I'll leave you two.

331
00:18:06,067 --> 00:18:07,767
I'll eat what you made
later, alright?

332
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:09,600
- Bye, Uncle!
- Good to see you.

333
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:16,533
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

334
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,167
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

335
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:25,567
[PHONE CHIMES]

336
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:43,200
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:18:52,133 --> 00:18:53,400
Kiko, don't just stand there!

338
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:56,267
You might be mistaken
for a bad person!

339
00:18:56,300 --> 00:18:57,367
Dude...

340
00:18:57,833 --> 00:18:59,500
Le-- let's just go home.

341
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:01,167
Huh?

342
00:19:01,167 --> 00:19:02,867
What about the curse?

343
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:06,600
Well, Jade didn't say whether
she's coming or not.

344
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,567
It's not like I can do
this alone.

345
00:19:10,133 --> 00:19:12,100
Well, that's a shame.

346
00:19:13,367 --> 00:19:15,833
- Sure you don't want to?
- Nah, let's just go home.

347
00:19:16,367 --> 00:19:18,667
- [JADE] Kiko!
- Oh, there she is!

348
00:19:18,667 --> 00:19:20,667
Kiko! Oh! [PANTING]

349
00:19:20,667 --> 00:19:23,233
Hi Cheska, I'm sorry.
Sorry I'm late.

350
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:26,333
[PANTING] I had lunch
before going here, sorry.

351
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:27,600
Is this the place?

352
00:19:29,233 --> 00:19:31,467
- [WHISPERS] Let's go home...
- But I thought--

353
00:19:31,467 --> 00:19:32,633
Well...

354
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:33,833
[BOTONG] Are you...

355
00:19:35,167 --> 00:19:36,933
my granddaughter's friends?

356
00:19:36,933 --> 00:19:40,767
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

357
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:42,300
Uh...

358
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:46,167
[STUTTERING] Ye-- Yes, Gramps.
We're Sari's friends.

359
00:19:46,167 --> 00:19:47,867
Are you the one who needs
to have their curse broken?

360
00:19:47,867 --> 00:19:50,400
Oh, not me! I'm not cursed
but they are!

361
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,300
- It's just them!
- Hey! Cheska...

362
00:19:54,433 --> 00:19:56,367
Gramps! Wha-- what are you
gonna do?

363
00:19:56,367 --> 00:19:57,633
- [BLADE SWISHES]
- I'll slash your curse off!

364
00:19:57,633 --> 00:19:59,333
- Wait!
- Don't, please!

365
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:05,267
[PLANT CRUNCHING]

366
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:06,667
[BOTONG] You may now
head inside.

367
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,367
Inside!

368
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:10,500
Go inside, he said.

369
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:13,267
- Inside.
- [WHISPERS] Sure, go on!

370
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:14,367
- Dude.
- Cheska!

371
00:20:14,367 --> 00:20:15,500
Yeah, I'm coming!

372
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:16,833
- You there.
- Me?

373
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:19,233
- Stay outside.
- Dude!

374
00:20:19,233 --> 00:20:21,467
Huh? Why?!

375
00:20:21,467 --> 00:20:24,367
The curse might transfer to you
once it's broken free from them.

376
00:20:24,367 --> 00:20:25,500
Is that what you want?

377
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,467
Oh, not at all, Gramps.

378
00:20:27,467 --> 00:20:30,233
I'm fine staying outside.
Hey Kiko, take care!

379
00:20:30,233 --> 00:20:31,333
Good luck!

380
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:32,933
Go!

381
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:37,533
Alright.

382
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:41,100
The next time Jade visits,
let me know.

383
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:42,733
So I can tell the maid

384
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,533
that you'll be in charge
of the cooking.

385
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:45,933
[SARCASTICALLY] Oh sure, Dad.

386
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:47,367
Tease me more.

387
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,700
No, I'm serious.

388
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:52,167
If I only knew, I could've had
the kitchen renovated.

389
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:53,900
[SCOFFS] Dad,
what are you even on?

390
00:20:54,033 --> 00:20:55,400
It's just a meal.

391
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,567
You say it's just a meal but...

392
00:20:57,700 --> 00:20:59,867
Didn't you have lunch
with her last time too?

393
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:03,100
It's just what we agreed on.
It's all part of a deal.

394
00:21:03,933 --> 00:21:05,433
What-- What deal?

395
00:21:06,267 --> 00:21:07,333
I saved her, right?

396
00:21:07,467 --> 00:21:08,833
Mm-hmm.

397
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,167
- Do you remember?
- Yes.

398
00:21:11,967 --> 00:21:14,033
She said she wanted
to make it up to me.

399
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:17,467
Said she wanted to pay back
the kindness I showed her, so...

400
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:19,500
It's one of the things
I asked from her.

401
00:21:19,633 --> 00:21:21,567
One of the things you asked?
[LAUGHS]

402
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:23,833
What else did you ask from her?

403
00:21:23,967 --> 00:21:25,100
[LAUGHS]

404
00:21:26,633 --> 00:21:28,667
Coffee for ten minutes.

405
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:31,667
Look, bud...

406
00:21:32,567 --> 00:21:34,767
Why don't you just
be honest with her?

407
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,000
Dad.

408
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:38,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

409
00:21:38,767 --> 00:21:40,400
I just wanted to help her.

410
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:45,667
She's going through a lot
so I just wanted to make sure...

411
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:47,800
that she's eating well.

412
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:52,267
[SIGHS] Do you hear yourself?

413
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:54,067
Not eating well?

414
00:21:55,733 --> 00:21:56,833
Bud.

415
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:58,667
The Alamzans have
a private chef.

416
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:02,333
And if I remember correctly,
her sister cooks as well.

417
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:04,467
And I've also heard
that the chef of Hotel 88

418
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:05,733
is also excellent

419
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:09,133
so food is the least
of her worries.

420
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:14,067
Dad... [SIGHS DEEPLY]

421
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,100
Okay, I won't bother you
anymore.

422
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,067
But,

423
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,500
for whatever it is,

424
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:22,233
whatever you have going on,

425
00:22:22,367 --> 00:22:23,900
I just want you to know that...

426
00:22:24,533 --> 00:22:25,700
I approve of her.

427
00:22:27,333 --> 00:22:28,400
- Okay?
- [SIGHS IN DISBELIEF]

428
00:22:28,533 --> 00:22:31,667
I approve of her, she's good

429
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:33,967
she's good
for our family and uh...

430
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:36,900
most importantly, she's good
for your heart.

431
00:22:37,033 --> 00:22:38,067
'Kay?

432
00:22:42,067 --> 00:22:49,033
[BOTONG HUMMING]

433
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:55,367
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

434
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:56,733
[COUGHS]

435
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:04,200
Seems like this isn't
your first time.

436
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:06,867
It's just similar to a facial
treatment at a salon, Kiko.

437
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:19,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

438
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:23,833
[LEON]<i> Roi is the only one
</i> that seems to have a motive.

439
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:26,267
<i>If only I could
find a connection</i>

440
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:28,100
<i> with what we did to Sandro...</i>

441
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:41,267
<i> A folder?</i>

442
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,167
<i> Uncle Mike has a folder?</i>

443
00:23:46,367 --> 00:23:47,733
<i> What's inside it?</i>

444
00:23:49,267 --> 00:23:52,133
<i>And why did he bring it
when he met up with Dad?</i>

445
00:23:52,267 --> 00:23:55,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

446
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:57,200
Leon.

447
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:59,267
Hey. Why're you here so early?

448
00:24:00,267 --> 00:24:02,267
I just left my power bank.

449
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,633
I came back to get it.

450
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:07,867
What's that?

451
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,333
Oh, nothing.

452
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:11,633
Just some business contracts.

453
00:24:11,767 --> 00:24:13,867
Business contract
that Dad left behind.

454
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:15,733
Can I see?

455
00:24:15,867 --> 00:24:17,333
Why?

456
00:24:17,467 --> 00:24:19,033
You won't understand it anyway.

457
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:24,167
Go on ahead,
get your power bank.

458
00:24:26,933 --> 00:24:28,033
Alright.

459
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:30,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

460
00:24:31,033 --> 00:24:32,100
[JUSTIN] This isn't
the first time

461
00:24:32,233 --> 00:24:34,467
<i>you're digging though
Dad's things.</i>

462
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,367
<i> What are you up to, Leon?</i>

463
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:43,367
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

464
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:47,667
<i> Are we cursed?</i>

465
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,967
<i>The two of you
have to do a ritual.</i>

466
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:52,733
<i>You shouldn't reveal this
to a single soul!</i>

467
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:53,800
<i> A leave of absence?!</i>

468
00:24:53,933 --> 00:24:55,633
<i>I just have to take care
of something.</i>

469
00:24:55,767 --> 00:24:58,233
<i>- And that is?
- If the ritual</i>

470
00:24:58,367 --> 00:24:59,933
<i>to remove the curse
becomes a success,</i>

471
00:25:00,067 --> 00:25:01,500
the opposite will happen to you.

472
00:25:01,633 --> 00:25:03,133
There will be a new connection.

473
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:05,300
<i>You'll just suddenly feel
something in your chest.</i>

474
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:07,867
<i>Something smells bad.
Like a dead body.</i>

475
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:09,667
<i> A dead body?</i>

